com.fortify.util.rest.query

Interface IRestConnectionQuery

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRestConnectionQuery, FoDEntityQuery, SSCEntityQuery

    public interface IRestConnectionQuery
    This interface allows for querying REST API's.
    Author:
    Ruud Senden

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      JSONList getAll()
      Get all results from the REST API call
      JSONMap getUnique()
      Get a unique result from the REST API call.

    • Method Detail

      • processAll

        void processAll(IJSONMapProcessor processor)
        Process all results from the REST API call. For large result sets, this method usually provides better performance and requires less memory than the getAll() method.
        Parameters:
        processor - used to process the results

      • processAll

        void processAll(Consumer<JSONMap> processor)
        Same as processAll(IJSONMapProcessor), but using lambda expressions.
        Parameters:
        processor - used to process the results

      • getAll

        JSONList getAll()
        Get all results from the REST API call
        Returns:
        JSONList containing all results from the REST API call

      • getUnique

        JSONMap getUnique()
        Get a unique result from the REST API call. If there are no results, null will be returned. If there is more than one result, an exception will be thrown.
        Returns:
        Unique result from the REST API call
